---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title={`About · ${SITE_TITLE}`} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>
      <h1>About Me</h1>

      <p>
        I'm a condensed matter physicist by training and a quantum infrastructure manager by day.
        I did my Ph.D. at Boston College under Ken Burch, working on 2D materials, topological
        superconductivity, and van der Waals heterostructures; basically, building tiny things
        out of atomically thin crystals and seeing what weird quantum stuff happens.
      </p>

      <p>
        These days I manage facilities, IT, safety, and logistics at the AWS Center for Quantum
        Computing. It's less glamorous than publishing in <em>Nature</em>, but someone has to
        make sure the dilution fridges stay cold and the cleanroom stays clean. I still miss
        being at the bench though, which is why my home lab keeps growing.
      </p>

      <p>
        Outside of work I'm a suburban dad with two kids, two dogs, and two cats; we're
        outnumbered and loving it. I build mechanical keyboards, tinker with 3D printers,
        and am slowly getting better at software (Python, some JS, enough to be dangerous).
        I devour sci-fi and epic fantasy novels, and I will absolutely watch construction
        YouTube at 11 PM instead of sleeping.
      </p>

      <p>
        This site is my corner of the internet to share publications, document projects,
        and occasionally write about whatever I'm building or breaking that week.
      </p>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>
